---
import Layout from '../../layouts/OpportunityPage.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Opportunities for K-12 Parents"
	description="Programs and resources for parents to support their children's journey into robotics and technology education."
	pubDate={new Date('January 01 2023')}
	heroImage={undefined}
>
	<div class="content-page">
		<header class="page-header">
			<h1>Opportunities for K-12 Parents</h1>
			<p class="page-description">
				Programs and resources for parents to support their children's journey into robotics and technology education.
			</p>
		</header>

		<section class="content-section">
			<p class="lead-text">
				Parents can enroll their children in these specialized programs that require parental consent and support.
			</p>
			
			<div class="opportunity-list">
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>Robotic Arts and Crafts workshop</h3>
					<p>A creative program that combines artistic expression with robotics fundamentals. Students build functional artistic robots while learning engineering principles.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>Summer Day Camp</h3>
					<p>Immersive week-long summer experience where students dive deep into robotics projects, make new friends with similar interests, and showcase their creations.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>Girl Scouts</h3>
					<p>Specialized robotics programs aligned with Girl Scout badges and achievements. These workshops help scouts earn technology and engineering badges while having fun.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="content-section">
			<h2>Parent Involvement</h2>
			<p>Ways you can support your child's robotics journey:</p>
			
			<div class="opportunity-list">
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>Parent Volunteer Program</h3>
					<p>Join our volunteer team to help with events, workshops, and competitions. No technical experience required - just enthusiasm and willingness to help!</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>Parent Information Sessions</h3>
					<p>Monthly sessions designed to help parents understand robotics education, career pathways, and how to support their children's interests.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>Family Robotics Days</h3>
					<p>Special events where families can work together on robotics projects, learn alongside their children, and celebrate achievements.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="content-section">
			<h2>Enrollment Information</h2>
			<p>Everything you need to know about enrolling your child in our programs:</p>
			
			<div class="opportunity-list">
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>Registration Process</h3>
					<p>Step-by-step guide to registering your child for our programs, including required forms, deadlines, and what to expect after registration.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>Consent Forms</h3>
					<p>All participating students need parental consent forms completed before attending any program. Forms can be completed online or in person.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>Scholarship Opportunities</h3>
					<p>Financial assistance is available for families who need support with program fees. Learn about our scholarship application process.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="content-section">
			<h2>Support Resources</h2>
			<p>Additional resources to help you support your child's interest in robotics:</p>
			
			<div class="opportunity-list">
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>Home Robotics Activities</h3>
					<p>Simple robotics projects you can do at home with common household materials to reinforce learning and spark creativity.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>Recommended Learning Resources</h3>
					<p>Curated list of books, websites, videos, and apps that complement our programs and support continued learning at home.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>Career Pathways Guide</h3>
					<p>Information about STEM careers and educational pathways to help you guide your child's long-term interests in technology and engineering.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="content-section">
			<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
			
			<div class="opportunity-list">
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>Is prior experience necessary?</h3>
					<p>No prior experience is necessary! Our programs are designed for all skill levels, from complete beginners to those with some robotics background.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>What safety measures are in place?</h3>
					<p>All our programs follow strict safety protocols. Staff are trained in first aid, all equipment is age-appropriate, and student-to-instructor ratios are maintained at optimal levels.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>How can I help if I don't have technical background?</h3>
					<p>You don't need technical expertise to support your child! Encouragement, helping with logistics, and showing interest in their projects are all valuable ways to contribute.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>

	<style>
		.opportunity-list {
			display: flex;
			flex-direction: column;
			gap: 1.5rem;
			margin-top: 2rem;
		}

		.opportunity-item {
			padding: 1.5rem;
			background: rgba(var(--accent-light), 0.05);
			border-radius: 12px;
			border: 1px solid rgba(var(--accent), 0.1);
			transition: all 0.3s ease;
		}

		.opportunity-item:hover {
			transform: translateY(-2px);
			box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(var(--accent), 0.1);
			background: rgba(var(--accent-light), 0.1);
		}

		.opportunity-item h3 {
			margin-top: 0;
			margin-bottom: 1rem;
			font-size: 1.25rem;
			color: var(--accent);
		}

		.opportunity-item p {
			margin-bottom: 0;
			font-size: 1rem;
		}
	</style>
</Layout>